"score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 4, "score_up": 257, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"twitter": {"quotedTweet": false, "images": false, "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 385, "created": 1778013589000, "id": "2051763820549308752", "video": {"preview": "https://pbs.twimg.com/tweet_video_thumb/HHlRxWZX0AYofcf.jpg", "mpeg": "", "aspectRatio": [76, 65], "heightRatio": 85, "type": "video/mp4", "url": "https://video.twimg.com/tweet_video/HHlRxWZX0AYofcf.mp4"}, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1468785657573163012/773F_ZRv_normal.jpg", "displayName": "Luke Rosiak", "username": "lukerosiak"}, "content": "You ain't seen nothin' yet on the Ohio home health fiasco. Part 2 drops now!\n\nOne landlord alone owns 7 buildings in Columbus containing 288 Medicaid firms that billed a quarter billion dollars. \n\nAnd boy, do the characters who are (supposed to be) inside have stories.", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 13344}}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASsL4BdJt", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 39, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8602585, "raw_content": "I pay income tax on my salary.\nI work hard and perform well so i am given stock awards.\nMy company sells a portion of those awards to cover taxes.\nThat sale becomes part of my 'income'.\nI have already paid taxes on the shares, but then when they vest, i can sell the existing shares that were granted, and at that point, i pay capital gains tax on the sale.\n\nNow let's say I decide to take the proceeds and invest them somewhere, oh let's say a savings account, a CD, or anything that earns a little interest.\nGuess what?  I pay taxes on the interest.  Why the fuck?  They've been taxed multiple times, not to mention they are considered part of my income when i sell them to take them out.  How many fucking times do we need to be taxed!!?!?!?!?!\nWe are literally taxed to death.\n\n", "author": "theycallmedon", "created": 1778076839160, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "wookiebush", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Explain this to me", "last_comment_created": 1778083023593, "content": "<p>I pay income tax on my salary.\nI work hard and perform well so i am given stock awards.\nMy company sells a portion of those awards to cover taxes.\nThat sale becomes part of my 'income'.\nI have already paid taxes on the shares, but then when they vest, i can sell the existing shares that were granted, and at that point, i pay capital gains tax on the sale.</p>\n<p>Now let's say I decide to take the proceeds and invest them somewhere, oh let's say a savings account, a CD, or anything that earns a little interest.\nGuess what?  I pay taxes on the interest.  Why the fuck?  They've been taxed multiple times, not to mention they are considered part of my income when i sell them to take them out.  How many fucking times do we need to be taxed!!?!?!?!?!\nWe are literally taxed to death.</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 11, "score_up": 39, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASsL4BuIn", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin":